{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_69","type":"command_execution","command":"/bin/bash -lc \"sed -n '1,260p' PR_COMMENTS.md\"","aggregated_output":"This change corrects the classification of `UBERON:0001629` (`carotid body`) in response to issue `#3591`.\n\nI removed the incorrect assertion that the carotid body is `part_of` `UBERON:0001530` (`common carotid artery plus branches`) and replaced it with `part_of UBERON:0000010` (`peripheral nervous system`), annotated with `PMID:32965908`. I also added `PMID:32965908` to the definition xrefs and linked the term back to the issue with `term_tracker_item`.\n\nRationale:\n- The issue text and the PubMed summary for `PMID:32965908` describe the carotid body as a sensory organ in the peripheral nervous system located in the adventitia at the carotid bifurcation.\n- Anatomical adjacency to the carotid arteries does not justify modeling the carotid body as part of the arterial tree.\n- The existing `is_a` placement under `UBERON:0034979` (`nonchromaffin paraganglion`) is consistent with the nervous-system interpretation, so the needed correction was the `part_of` relation.\n\nChecks completed:\n- Reviewed the current stanzas for `UBERON:0001629`, `UBERON:0001530`, `UBERON:0034979`, and `UBERON:0000010`.\n- Checked comparable `part_of UBERON:0000010` usage in the ontology for consistency.\n- Attempted to use `aurelian fulltext PMID:32965908`; the helper was not installed in this environment, so I used the PubMed record summary instead.\n- Edited through the standard `obo-checkout.pl` / `obo-checkin.pl` workflow.\n- Reserialized `src/ontology/uberon-edit.obo` with `robot convert`.\n- Re-ran `robot convert` to `/tmp/uberon-validate.obo` as a non-destructive validation pass.\n\nLocal commit:\n- `75d0673` `Fix carotid body nervous system classification`\n","exit_code":0,"status":"completed"}}
